<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Representing vectors geometrically</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Consider the points <b>P({@x1@}, {@y1@})</b> and <b>Q({@x2@}, {@y2@})</b> in a 2D Cartesian plane. The vector <b>\(\vec{PQ}\)</b> represents the displacement from P to Q.</p>

[[jsxgraph width="400px" height="400px"]]
var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {
    boundingbox: [-1, 12, 12, -1], 
    axis: true, 
    showCopyright: false
});

var p1 = board.create('point', [{#x1#}, {#y1#}], {name: 'P', size: 3, fixed: true});
var p2 = board.create('point', [{#x2#}, {#y2#}], {name: 'Q', size: 3, fixed: true});
var vec = board.create('arrow', [p1, p2], {strokeColor: 'blue', strokeWidth: 3, withLabel: true});

// Component guidelines
board.create('segment', [[{#x1#}, {#y1#}], [{#x2#}, {#y1#}]], {dash: 2, strokeColor: 'gray'});
board.create('segment', [[{#x2#}, {#y1#}], [{#x2#}, {#y2#}]], {dash: 2, strokeColor: 'gray'});
[[/jsxgraph]]


<ol>
    <li>Determine the components of \(\vec{PQ}\): <br>
        \(\vec{PQ}\) =  [[input:ans1]] \(, \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]
    </li>
    <li>Calculate the magnitude of \(\vec{PQ}\): <br>
        \(|\vec{PQ}| = \) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]
    </li>
</ol>

<ol start="3">
<li> <p>Given another vector \(b = ({@bx@}, {@by@})\)</b>, find the resultant vector \(R\) where \(R= \vec{PQ} + b\).</p>  
    <p>\(R = \) [[input:ans4]] \(, \) [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]] [[validation:ans5]][[feedback:prt5]]</p></li>
</ol>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<b>Step 1: Determine the components of \(\vec{PQ}\)</b>
\(\begin{align}
\vec{PQ} &= (x_Q - x_P, y_Q - y_P) \\
&= ({@x2@} - {@x1@}, {@y2@} - {@y1@}) \\
&= {@ta1@}, {@ta2@}
\end{align}\)

<b>Step 2: Calculate the magnitude \(|\vec{PQ}|\)</b>
\(\begin{align}
|\vec{PQ}| &= \sqrt{{@ta1@}^2 + {@ta2@}^2} \\
&= \sqrt{{@mag_sq@}} \\
&= {@ta3@}
\end{align}\)

<b>Step 3: Add corresponding components for \(\mathbf{R}\)</b>
\(\begin{align}
\mathbf{R} &= \vec{PQ} + \mathbf{b} \\
&= ({@ta1@} + {@bx@}, {@ta2@} + {@by@}) \\
&= {@ta4@}, {@ta5@}
\end{align}\)]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
